lead_paragraph: Because of an editing error, an article on Monday about the United States Figure Skating Championships referred incorrectly to the previous top accomplishments of Brandon Mroz, an 18-year-old high school senior who finished second. He was second twice at the junior national championships — not at the world junior championships, where he was fourth the past two years.
